  // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  // §M REGALIA — combo & head jewelry (the "magic boosts vs metal armour" loadout fork). All set with
  // ATTUNED gems at the lapidary (gate: attunement) and grant transient buff conditions while worn.
  //   • CROWNS/CIRCLETS/DIADEMS sit in `headOuter` — the HELMET slot — so a buff crown means NO helm
  //     (the explicit head-armour trade). Token defense only.
  //   • TORCS/PENDANTS use the `amulet` (neck-jewelry) slot; COMBO RINGS use `ring`.
  //   • Combo pieces list TWO conditions (two attuned gems): one slot, two buffs — strong but costly.
  // `grace` (dodge) / `fortitude` (endurance) are the defensive buffs — magic as an alternative to armour.
  // ── Crowns / circlets / diadems (headOuter; competes with helmets) ──
